==English==

===Etymology===
From ''[[plumbum]]''.

===Adjective===
'''plumbic'''
# {{chemistry}} Of, pertaining to, resembling, or containing, [[lead]]; -- used specifically to designate those [[compound]]s in which it has a higher [[valence]] as contrasted with [[plumbous]] compounds; as, [[plumbic oxide]].

